b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe46027.htm)  [Next](sbe46029.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543983846/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_Vedic Hymns, Part II (SBE46)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg [1897], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 102\n\n### MA _N_ _D_ ALA I, HYMN 78.\n\n#### ASH _T_ AKA I, ADHY\xc3\x82YA 5, VARGA 26.\n\n1\\. O _G_ atavedas, who dwellest among all tribes, we the Gotamas (praise)\nthee with our song--we praise thee aloud with (songs full of) splendour.\n\n2\\. Gotama [1](sbe46028.htm#an_1:78:2:1) desirous of riches exalts thee, as\nthou art, with his song. We praise thee aloud with (songs full of) splendour.\n\n3\\. We call thee, such as thou art, the highest winner of booty, as A\xe1\xb9\x85giras\ndid. We praise thee aloud with (songs full of) splendour.\n\n4\\. (We praise) thee, the greatest destroyer of enemies (or, of V _ri_ tra),\nwho hurlest the Dasyus away--we praise thee, such as thou art, aloud with\n(songs full of) splendour.\n\n5\\. We the Rahuga _n_ as [1](sbe46028.htm#an_1:78:5:1) have recited a honey-\nsweet speech to Agni. We praise thee aloud with (songs full of) splendour.\n\n#### NOTES.\n\nThe same _Ri_ shi. Metre, Gayatri.\n\n##### Verse 2.\n\nNote 1. This probably means, 'the descendant of Gotama.' See Zeitschrift der\nD. Morg. Gesellschaft, XLII, 202.\n\n##### Verse 5.\n\nNote 1. The Rahuga _n_ as seem to be a branch of the Gotamas; see \xc3\x82 _s_\nvalayana _S_ rautasutra XII, 11, 1.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 79](sbe46029.htm)\n\n"